; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>Ideas in a=
n Idea Lab are treated like hypotheses, which means people are always looki=
ng for opportunities to test what they&#8217;ve been thinking about. Idea L=
abs are the perfect boxing ring for that testing.</em></p></blockquote><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The fact that Techno-Optimistic Media is small, that it=
 doesn&#8217;t appeal to a mass audience, is a feature, not a bug. Going bi=
g &#8211; and diluting the audience &#8211; would kill that vibe, and when =
you strike upon scenius, Kelly says: </span><em>The best you can do is NOT =
KILL IT.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You&#8217;ll have to go big eventually, =
if you want to be big, but there&#8217;s real value in beating up your idea=
s in small Idea Labs and competitively friendly scenes.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Our advice is not as blunt as &#8220;don&#8217;t work with the ma=
ss media.&#8221; It&#8217;s not that simple &#8211; because the mass media =
can actually be extremely good at what they do.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
<span>The trick is trying to speak to the </span><strong>right audiences</s=
trong><span> at the </span><strong>right times </strong><span>on the </span=
><strong>right channels</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">H=
ere&#8217;s what that looks like in practice.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-=
