nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><=
em>I think a good checkpoint [for whether you&#8217;re ready to start a com=
pany] is: &#8216;Have you annoyed your friends about this idea enough?&#821=
7; And I definitely did&#8230; Because if it sticks in your head, and you&#=
8217;re not being dissuaded. San Francisco is an amazing place for people w=
ho are positive about startup ideas. But if you talk to highly technical pe=
ople about stuff like this, they will poke holes in everything. And if you =
can survive the thunderdome of that, and keep annoying your friends about i=
t, maybe you should consider doing that idea.</em></p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Surviving the thunderdome is a perfect encapsulation of our idea.=
 Your storytelling journey should be like surviving a series of increasingl=
y thunderous thunderdomes, starting with friends, then branching outwards. =
At some point, you&#8217;ll want to go public, both to attract people and b=
attletest your ideas.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Nobody can change the worl=
d in a vacuum. You have to convince people to work with you; investors to g=
ive you money; customers to buy your product; and so on, at every scale.</p=
><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;">This is, ultimately, the most fundamental job of a found=
er &#8212; to share a compelling story that convinces people to hitch their=
 wagons to yours.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">And there is no possible way to outs=
ource that task.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>As former Anduril comms lead Lu=
lu Cheng Meservey wrote in her must-read </span><em><a href=3D"https://subs=
tack.com/redirect/b46cbbd0-2dec-4dd6-b682-9b466eae067a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Inside Anduril&#8217;s Comms Strateg=
y: 10 Rules for Mission-Driven Founders</a></em><span>, &#8220;Going direct=
 means retaining control over your message by speaking directly to your aud=
ience instead of depending on middlemen. This is mandatory for mission-driv=
en founders.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fon=
